Describe a time you made a decision to wait for something
- when it happened
- who you were with
- what you were waiting for
- explain how you felt about the decision

I’d like to talk about a time when I decided to wait before buying something, which was a new phone.

This happened about four years ago, when I was thinking of upgrading my phone. At that time, many stores were offering big discounts on the iPhone 13 Pro Max, so it seemed like a really good deal. I had also watched a lot of reviews, and most of them said it was still a great option.

However, I was more interested in the newer iPhone 14 Pro Max because I preferred its design. The problem was that it was more expensive and also out of stock, so I would have to wait for quite a while.

I remember spending several days thinking carefully about whether I should go for the cheaper option or wait for the one I really wanted. In the end, I decided to wait, because I felt that if I was going to spend a large amount of money, I should choose something I truly liked.

To be honest, it wasn’t an easy decision. At first, I felt quite impatient, especially when I saw other people already using new phones. But over time, I became more confident that I had made the right choice.

Looking back, I think this experience taught me to be more patient and to think more carefully before making important decisions.